President Obama met with members of the Congressional Black Caucus (CBC) to discuss various topics including the economy, criminal justice reform, and trade. The President praised the CBC for their efforts in addressing important issues and emphasized the need to build on the legislative progress made in the past six years. He expressed concern about the unemployment rate among African Americans and reaffirmed his commitment to supporting policies that help working families. The President also highlighted the importance of criminal justice reform and building trust between communities and law enforcement. He discussed his trade agenda and asked for the CBC's support. The meeting concluded with the President thanking the CBC and expressing his desire to continue working with them.